# Mobile App Development Rules

## React Native & Expo Setup
- **Framework**: Expo SDK ~50.0.11 with React Native
- **Navigation**: React Navigation v6 with bottom tabs and native stack
- **State management**: Zustand for global state
- **Testing**: Jest with extensive React Native mocking

## Mobile-Specific Dependencies
- **Audio**: expo-av for audio playback
- **UI**: React Native components with Expo vector icons
- **Navigation**: @react-navigation packages
- **Storage**: AsyncStorage for local data persistence

## Mobile App Structure
- **Entry point**: [mobile-app/App.tsx](mdc:mobile-app/App.tsx)
- **Configuration**: [mobile-app/app.json](mdc:mobile-app/app.json)
- **Package management**: Separate [mobile-app/package.json](mdc:mobile-app/package.json)

## Development Commands
- **Start**: `cd mobile-app && npm start`
- **Android**: `cd mobile-app && npm run android`
- **iOS**: `cd mobile-app && npm run ios`
- **Build**: `cd mobile-app && npm run build:android/ios`

## Mobile Testing Patterns
- **Extensive mocking**: All React Native modules mocked in [mobile-app/jest.setup.js](mdc:mobile-app/jest.setup.js)
- **Expo mocking**: expo-av, expo-constants, expo-font mocked
- **Navigation mocking**: React Navigation components mocked
- **Platform mocking**: Platform-specific code mocked

## Mobile UI Guidelines
- **Responsive design**: Use Flexbox and responsive dimensions
- **Platform differences**: Handle iOS/Android differences appropriately
- **Performance**: Optimize for mobile performance and memory usage
- **Accessibility**: Implement proper accessibility features

## Mobile-Specific Features
- **Audio playback**: Use expo-av for background audio
- **Deep linking**: Implement proper deep linking with expo-linking
- **Push notifications**: Use Expo notifications for mobile alerts
- **Offline support**: Implement offline-first data strategies